<biogHist>
<abstract>The Preventive Payment Scheme was designed to prevent children going into residential care by making payments to families undergoing a serious financial crisis. The Commonwealth government funded it. In 1979-80, the State government replaced it with a Family Assistance Scheme which operated similarly.</abstract>

</biogHist>
